author: Brenda Goh
title: Postcards from Wuhan: residents tell the world to stay strong, stay indoors
description: Life in the Chinese city of Wuhan, where the coronavirus first emerged, is slowly returning to normal as the government relaxes a more than two-month-old lockdown that cut the city off from the world and kept most of its 11 million residents at home.
